---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import RelatedWorkflows from '../../components/RelatedWorkflows.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Workflows', url: '/workflows' },
  { name: 'Rearing Protocols', url: '/workflows/rearing-protocols' }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'What are rearing protocols?',
    answer: 'Rearing protocols are structured developmental programs for young animals. They include exercises, socialization activities, and handling routines designed to produce well-adjusted, confident animals. Examples range from ENS and ESI for puppies to foal imprinting for horses, bottle kid schedules for goats, and kitten socialization programs for cats.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What benchmark protocols are included?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ includes industry-standard protocols like ENS (Early Neurological Stimulation), ESI (Early Scent Introduction), Rule of 7s, and developmental stage programs for dogs. For other species, you can build custom protocols using the Protocol Builder or import community-shared protocols from breeders in your species.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I create my own custom protocols?',
    answer: 'Yes. The Protocol Builder lets you create custom protocols with your own phases, tasks, and timing. This is especially valuable for species like horses, goats, sheep, cats, and rabbits where standardized published protocols are less common. Start from scratch or modify existing protocols to match your program.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How does per-animal tracking work?',
    answer: 'Each offspring gets individual progress tracking. You can mark tasks complete for the whole group at once (batch completion) or track exceptions for individuals who missed or could not complete specific exercises.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What is community protocol sharing?',
    answer: 'Experienced breeders can share their custom protocols with the community. Other breeders can browse, rate, review, and import protocols that work well. Whether you raise dogs, horses, goats, or any other species, you can learn from breeders who have refined their approach over years.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How do completion certificates work?',
    answer: 'When an animal completes a protocol, you can generate a digital certificate documenting their developmental program. Certificates include a verification code buyers can use to confirm authenticity. Great for demonstrating the care that went into raising each animal.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What temperament and aptitude tests are available?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ includes the Puppy Aptitude Test (PAT) for general temperament evaluation, a Gun Dog Aptitude Test for sporting dog evaluation, and Working-Dog Role Suitability analysis. For other species, you can create custom evaluation frameworks using the Protocol Builder.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can buyers see assessment results?',
    answer: 'Yes. You control which results are shared. When you mark an assessment as buyer-visible, it appears in the Buyer Portal with radar charts, interpretations, and placement recommendations. Buyers can see the data that helps them understand their animal before going home.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Do I need to use protocols to use BreederHQ?',
    answer: 'No. Protocols are optional. Many breeders start without them and add protocols later as their program matures. The rest of BreederHQ works independently of the protocol system.'
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Rearing Protocols & Developmental Tracking | BreederHQ"
  description="Structured development programs for puppies, foals, kittens, kids, and lambs: built-in protocols, per-animal tracking, and buyer certificates. See how."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <a href="#main-content" class="skip-link sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:absolute focus:top-4 focus:left-4 focus:z-50 focus:px-4 focus:py-2 focus:bg-white focus:text-black focus:shadow-lg focus:rounded">
    Skip to content
  </a>

  <main id="main-content">
  <nav class="breadcrumb py-4 px-4 bg-gray-50" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <ol class="flex items-center space-x-2 max-w-4xl mx-auto text-sm">
      <li><a href="/" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Home</a></li>
      <li class="text-gray-400">›</li>
      <li><a href="/workflows" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Workflows</a></li>
      <li class="text-gray-400">›</li>
      <li aria-current="page" class="text-gray-600">Rearing Protocols</li>
    </ol>
  </nav>

  <!-- Section 1: Hero -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-6">Structured Development. Documented Results.</h1>

      <aside class="tldr-box bg-gray-100 border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] p-6 my-8 rounded" role="complementary" aria-label="Page summary">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Quick Summary</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          You already invest time in developing your young animals. ENS and socialization for puppies, imprinting and halter training for foals, handling protocols for kids, lambs, kittens, and kits. BreederHQ tracks it all: built-in protocols, custom protocol builder, per-animal progress tracking, community sharing, and verification certificates for buyers.
        </p>
      </aside>

      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        You already put real effort into developing your young animals. Whether it's structured neurological stimulation for puppies, imprint training for foals, or handling and socialization for kittens, kids, or lambs, that work matters.
      </p>

      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        BreederHQ helps you track it, prove it, and share it with buyers. No more paper checklists or spreadsheets.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: The Problem -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">You already do the work. The tracking is the hard part.</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        You've built your developmental routines over years of experience. The challenge isn't the protocols themselves, it's keeping track of everything:
      </p>

      <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700 mb-8">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Paper checklists get lost, wet, or illegible</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Spreadsheets work until you have multiple groups overlapping</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Buyers ask what you did, but you have no easy way to show them</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>When an animal misses an exercise, you lose track of what to make up</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>New staff or helpers don't know what was already completed</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>You spend more time tracking than actually doing the exercises</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div class="bg-white border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] p-6 rounded">
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 font-semibold">
          You put in the effort. BreederHQ makes sure there's a record of it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: Protocol Library -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Industry-Standard Protocols Built-In</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        BreederHQ includes benchmark protocols for dogs and a custom protocol builder for any species. Assign a protocol to your group and start tracking.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">🐕 Dog Protocols (Built-In)</h3>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">🧠 Early Neurological Stimulation (ENS)</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            Five exercises performed daily from days 3-16 to improve stress tolerance, cardiovascular performance, and disease resistance.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li>• Tactile stimulation</li>
            <li>• Head held erect</li>
            <li>• Head pointed down</li>
            <li>• Supine position</li>
            <li>• Thermal stimulation</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">👃 Early Scent Introduction (ESI)</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            Expose puppies to novel scents daily from days 3-16. Develops scent discrimination and confidence with new stimuli.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li>• One new scent per day</li>
            <li>• Track reactions (positive/neutral/negative)</li>
            <li>• Build scent exposure library</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">7️⃣ Rule of 7s</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            By 7 weeks, puppies should have experienced 7 different surfaces, 7 different locations, 7 different toys, and more.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li>• 7 surfaces (grass, concrete, carpet, etc.)</li>
            <li>• 7 locations</li>
            <li>• 7 challenges/obstacles</li>
            <li>• 7 different food containers</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">📚 More Dog Protocols</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            Additional built-in programs:
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li>• Developmental stage programs</li>
            <li>• Enrichment and exposure exercises</li>
            <li>• Startle/recovery exercises</li>
            <li>• Sound desensitization protocols</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">🐴🐐🐱🐇🐑 Other Species (Custom Protocol Builder)</h3>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Published protocol standards vary by species. The Protocol Builder lets you create exactly what your program needs. Here are examples of what breeders are tracking:
      </p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">🐴 Horses</h4>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li>• Foal imprint training (first 24-48 hours)</li>
            <li>• Halter breaking and leading</li>
            <li>• Farrier desensitization</li>
            <li>• Trailer loading introduction</li>
            <li>• Grooming and handling milestones</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">🐐 Goats & 🐑 Sheep</h4>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li>• Bottle kid/lamb feeding schedules</li>
            <li>• Disbudding and banding timelines</li>
            <li>• Halter training and handling</li>
            <li>• Hoof care introduction</li>
            <li>• Weaning protocols</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">🐱 Cats</h4>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li>• Kitten socialization windows</li>
            <li>• Handling and gentling routines</li>
            <li>• Litter training milestones</li>
            <li>• Sound and environment exposure</li>
            <li>• Multi-pet household prep</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">🐇 Rabbits</h4>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li>• Handling and gentling protocols</li>
            <li>• Cage and enclosure introduction</li>
            <li>• Nail trim conditioning</li>
            <li>• Socialization with people and sounds</li>
            <li>• Weaning and diet transition</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Each protocol includes day-by-day tasks, timing windows, and completion criteria. Use the built-in protocols or build your own for any species.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: Custom Protocol Builder -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Build Your Own Protocols</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Every program is different. Maybe you've developed your own approach over years of breeding. Maybe you combine elements from multiple systems. Maybe your breed has specific developmental needs.
      </p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        The Protocol Builder lets you create exactly what your program needs:
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Protocol Builder Features</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">✓</span>
            <span><strong>Phases:</strong> Organize tasks into developmental stages (neonatal, transitional, socialization, etc.)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">✓</span>
            <span><strong>Tasks:</strong> Define specific activities with descriptions, timing, and frequency</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">✓</span>
            <span><strong>Day ranges:</strong> Specify when each task should be performed (e.g., days 3-16)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">✓</span>
            <span><strong>Notes/instructions:</strong> Add detailed guidance for each task</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">✓</span>
            <span><strong>Drag-and-drop reordering:</strong> Easily adjust task sequence</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Start from scratch, or clone an existing protocol and modify it. Your custom protocols work exactly like the built-in ones-full tracking, certificates, everything.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 5: Per-Puppy Tracking -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Track Every Animal, Every Task</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Real life doesn't follow perfect schedules. One offspring might be sick during an exercise. Another might need extra attention. The tracking system handles real-world messiness, whether you're managing a litter of ten puppies, triplet kids, twin lambs, or a single foal.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Batch Completion</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Completed today's exercises with the whole group? Mark the task done for everyone at once. No need to check individual boxes one by one.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Individual Tracking</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Need to track one animal differently? Each offspring has their own completion record. Perfect for animals with different developmental timelines.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Exception Handling</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            When an animal misses a task, log it as an exception with a reason. "Blue collar missed Day 5 handling due to vet visit." The system tracks what needs to be made up.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Progress Dashboard</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            See group-wide and per-animal completion percentages at a glance. Know exactly where each offspring stands in their developmental program.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)]">
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">
          <strong>For helpers and staff:</strong> Anyone you authorize can log completions. They see today's tasks, mark them done, and add notes. No confusion about what's been done.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 6: Community Sharing -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Learn from the Best Breeders</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        The breeding community thrives on shared knowledge. Community Protocol Sharing lets experienced breeders share what works-and lets everyone benefit.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-6 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Share Your Protocols</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            Developed a protocol that produces exceptional results? Share it with the community. Your protocol gets attributed to you, building your reputation as a knowledgeable breeder.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
            You control visibility: keep protocols private, share with specific breeders, or publish publicly.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Browse and Import</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            Find protocols from experienced breeders in your breed or discipline. Filter by species, breed, purpose, and ratings. Import protocols with one click and customize for your program.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Ratings and Reviews</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            Rate protocols 1-5 stars. Leave reviews about what worked and what didn't. The best protocols rise to the top. New breeders can trust community-vetted approaches.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Export and Backup</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Export your protocols to a file. Back them up, share via email, or import into another breeder's account. Your work isn't locked in.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed font-semibold">
        Community sharing and all other protocol features are included on Pro and Enterprise plans.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 7: Completion Certificates -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Show Buyers the Care You've Already Put In</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Buyers want to know their animal was raised right. Completion certificates provide documented proof of the developmental work you've done, giving you a way to show it, not just say it.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white border-2 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] rounded-lg p-8 mb-8">
        <div class="text-center mb-6">
          <div class="text-5xl mb-4">🏅</div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">Certificate of Completion</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Each certificate includes:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-6">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">✓</span>
            <span>Animal name and identification</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">✓</span>
            <span>Protocol name and description</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">✓</span>
            <span>Completion date and percentage</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">✓</span>
            <span>Breeder name and program</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">✓</span>
            <span><strong>Verification code</strong> for authenticity checking</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded text-center">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-1">Verification Code</p>
          <code class="text-lg font-mono">BHQ-ENS-2026-XXXX-XXXX</code>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">For Breeders</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Differentiate from breeders who don't document development</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Justify premium pricing with documented care</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Include in go-home packets alongside health records</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">For Buyers</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Verify certificates are authentic, not fabricated</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Understand exactly what developmental work was done</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Trust that the breeder invested in early development</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 7b: Buyer Portal Integration -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Share the Results with Buyers</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        The work you put into early development deserves to be seen. BreederHQ gives you two ways to share it:
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Completion Certificates</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            When an animal completes a protocol, generate a digital certificate with a verification code. Buyers can verify authenticity online. Include certificates in your go-home documentation to show the care behind every animal.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
            Builds trust and justifies premium pricing.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Training Protocols in the Buyer Portal</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            After placement, buyers can access training protocols you assign through their <a href="/workflows/client-portal" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Buyer Portal</a>. They can log their own progress on continued socialization, training milestones, and other activities you recommend.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
            Keeps the developmental journey going beyond your program.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 8: Temperament Testing Integration -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Temperament and Aptitude Testing</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Rearing protocols develop your animals. Temperament testing evaluates them. BreederHQ includes <strong>built-in assessments for dogs</strong> plus a custom evaluation builder for any species, so you can match every animal to the right home.
      </p>

      <!-- PAT -->
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">🐕 Dog Assessments (Built-In)</h3>
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 mb-6">
        <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Puppy Aptitude Test (PAT)</h4>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          The industry standard for evaluating puppy temperament. Administered at 49 days (7 weeks), the PAT scores each puppy across 10 standardized tests on a 1-6 scale:
        </p>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-gray-700">
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-start"><span class="mr-3">1.</span><span>Social Attraction</span></li>
