  <section class="py-20 px-4 faq-section">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-12">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>What are rearing protocols?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Rearing protocols are structured developmental programs for young animals. They include exercises, socialization activities, and handling routines designed to produce well-adjusted, confident animals. Examples range from ENS and ESI for puppies to foal imprinting for horses, bottle kid schedules for goats, and kitten socialization programs for cats.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>What benchmark protocols are included?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>BreederHQ includes industry-standard protocols like ENS, ESI, Rule of 7s, and developmental stage programs for dogs. For other species, you can build custom protocols using the Protocol Builder or import community-shared protocols from breeders in your species.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>Can I create my own custom protocols?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. The Protocol Builder lets you create custom protocols with your own phases, tasks, and timing. You can start from scratch or modify existing protocols to match your program's approach.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>How does per-animal tracking work?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Each offspring gets individual progress tracking. You can mark tasks complete for the whole group at once (batch completion) or track exceptions for individuals who missed or could not complete specific exercises.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>How do completion certificates work?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>When an animal completes a protocol, you can generate a digital certificate documenting their developmental program. Certificates include a verification code buyers can use to confirm authenticity. Great for demonstrating the care that went into raising each animal.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>What temperament and aptitude tests are available?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>BreederHQ includes the Puppy Aptitude Test (PAT) for general temperament evaluation, the Gun Dog Aptitude Test for sporting dog evaluation, and Working-Dog Role Suitability analysis. For other species, you can create custom evaluation frameworks using the Protocol Builder.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>Can buyers see assessment results?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. You control which results are shared. When you mark an assessment as buyer-visible, it appears in the Buyer Portal with radar charts, interpretations, and placement recommendations. Buyers can see the data that helps them understand their animal before going home.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
